description: From Latin viminalis (“pertaining to osiers”), from vimen (“a pliant twig, osier”).

adjectives.description: viminal (comparative more viminal, superlative most viminal)

entries.meaning: (rare) Of or pertaining to twigs; consisting of twigs; producing twigs.
examples: The plantation was then a model of beauty and vigorous health, clothed in a dense viminal mass.
